# Self-Testing Checklist — Mandatory Before Completion

After completing any non-trivial task (feature, bug fix, refactor), execute this checklist BEFORE presenting the result. DO NOT skip any section.

## 1. Code Quality

- [ ] No function > 40 lines without justification
- [ ] No duplicated logic — shared code extracted
- [ ] Error cases handled with try/catch or error boundaries
- [ ] Semantic naming (no `tmp`, `data1`, `doStuff`)

## 2. React Check (skip if no component code touched)

- [ ] No inline `?? []` / `?? {}` in render — use module-level constants or `useMemo`
- [ ] No new object/array creation in render paths feeding dependency arrays
- [ ] All `useMemo`/`useCallback` dependency arrays correct

## 3. Cross-Platform Impact (skip if single-platform file)

- [ ] Identified which platforms consume modified code
- [ ] UI changes verified on mobile (narrowest) and desktop (widest)
- [ ] Stated: "Affects: [platforms]" and "Does NOT affect: [platforms]"

## 4. Business Logic & Regression

- [ ] Implementation matches original requirement
- [ ] Edge cases covered: empty data, null, loading, error states
- [ ] Data flow end-to-end: API → state → UI
- [ ] Shared hook/utility modified → checked all consumers
- [ ] Type definitions changed → all consumers updated
- [ ] State atoms modified → verified all readers/writers

## 5. Potential Bugs (skip for docs/config-only changes)

- [ ] No race conditions in async operations
- [ ] No stale closures capturing outdated state
- [ ] No memory leaks: subscriptions/listeners cleaned up
- [ ] No infinite loops from useEffect dependency chains
- [ ] "Not loaded" (`null`/`undefined`) vs "empty" (`[]`) properly distinguished

## 6. Unit Tests (skip for pure UI styling with no logic)

- [ ] New/modified logic has corresponding `.test.ts` file
- [ ] Tests cover happy path AND edge cases (empty, null, error)
- [ ] Bug fix includes a regression test
- [ ] Tests pass: `yarn test -- --testPathPattern=<path>`

## 7. Lint & Type Check

- [ ] `ReadLints` shows no new errors on modified files
- [ ] `yarn lint:staged` passes
- [ ] `yarn tsc:staged` passes

## 8. Manual Verification (skip for non-UI changes)

- Which command to run (`yarn app:ios` / `yarn app:desktop` / `yarn app:web` / `yarn app:ext`)
- Which page to open and what action to perform
- What the expected behavior is
- Edge cases to check: empty state, error state, loading state

## 9. Summary Output

Present to user:
1. **What was done** — 1-2 sentences
2. **Files modified/created**
3. **Tests added/updated**
4. **Impact scope** — affected / not affected platforms
5. **Risk assessment** — areas needing manual verification
6. **Self-test result** — which checks passed, which were skipped and why

## Bug Fix Case Recording

After every **bug fix**, append to `.claude/skills/1k-retrospective/references/case-studies.md`:

```
## Case: [Title]
**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD | **Platforms**: [affected]
**Symptom**: [what the user saw]
**Root Cause**: [what was actually wrong]
**Fix**: [what was changed]
**Catchable by**: [Section N: check item, or "NEW — not covered"]
```

Do NOT modify this file directly — only append to `case-studies.md`.

## Skip Rules

- Sections 2, 3, 5, 6, 8: see "skip if" notes in each section header
- NEVER skip Sections 1, 4, 7, and 9
